SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 476
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Vicki Davis, 2024–2025
Sam Houston Elementary School Teacher of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding teachers
who have devoted their careers to providing the highest-quality education for Tennessee's
students; and
WHEREAS, Vicki Davis is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself
as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Davis has been named the 2024–2025 Teacher of the Year at Sam
Houston Elementary School, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive influence she
has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, an educator for twenty years, Vicki Davis serves as a kindergarten teacher;
she holds bachelor's and master's degrees in special education as well as an elementary
education endorsement; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Davis serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike, and
her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Vicki Davis truly epitomizes the dedicated teacher who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Vicki Davis on being
chosen as the 2024–2025 Teacher of the Year at Sam Houston Elementary School, commend
her exceptional service to the children of Tennessee, salute her professional expertise and
personal excellence, and wish her all the best in her future endeavors.
